Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Namibia  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The famous work of Kim Jong Il "Socialism Is a Science" was brought out in booklet by the Capital Publishing House in Windhoek, Namibia on April 13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work published on November 1, Juche 83 (1994) clarifies the idea that Korean-style socialism based on the Juche-oriented socialist theory is the most scientific and vital socialism and principled issues in defending socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The booklet in its preface said that the society desired by humankind is socialism and this ideal society has become a reality in the DPRK. Any visitor to the DPRK will have an opportunity to see for himself a great country where everybody leads an optimistic, happy and harmonious life under the socialist system, receiving huge benefits including free medical care and free education unimaginable in other societies, the booklet added.

Kim Jong Il Praised by American Study Organization  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics posted pictures of Kim Jong Il and special articles on its Internet e-theoretical magazine "Red Banner of Songun" on April 7 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of his election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article entitled "Overall succession to the cause of the army, election of NDC chairman" noted that Kim Jong Il has led the stand-off with the U.S. to victory, demonstrating his great personality as an invincible and iron-willed brilliant commander before the whole world. He enjoys absolute trust, boundless reverence and full support from the whole party, the entire army and all the people of the DPRK, it said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK led by Kim Jong Il has emerged a bulwark of global independence and the cause of socialism, and a model of anti-imperialist, anti-U.S. struggle, shedding its rays all over the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another article titled "Praise from humankind" said the 21st century will shine as a century of Kim Jong Il, noting that he is recognized by the world community as an outstanding leader of the socialist movement in the 21st century.

Pyongyang Declaration Supported  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- C. P. Mainali, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist), and Bonakele Majuba, secretary of the Mfumalanga Provincial Committee of the South African Communist Party who is chairman of the South African Association of Friendship and Solidarity with Korean People, separately made public statements on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of the publication of the Pyongyang Declaration on April 15 and 13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In their statements they noted that the Pyongyang Declaration is displaying ever-increasing justice and vitality and dynamically inspiring the world progressive people aspiring after socialism to struggles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed the belief that the desire of humankind for socialism is sure to come true as long as Kim Jong Il develops socialist Korea and steers the world socialist movement.

Korean Book, Photo and Handicraft Exhibitions Open in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- Korean book, photo and handicraft exhibitions opened in Russia, Venezuela and Uganda on April 10 and 11 on the occasions of the Day of the Sun, the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and the 75th founding anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the exhibitions were works of the peerlessly great men, photos showing their immortal exploits, and other books, photos and handicrafts introducing the Korean people in their efforts to accelerate socialist construction under the banner of Songun, their resourcefulness and talents. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the opening ceremonies of the exhibitions were personages and people from all walks of life of those countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Delegates of the 14th Congress of the Women's International Democratic Federation (WIDF) were present at the opening ceremony of the exhibition held in Venezuela. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the opening ceremonies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president of the WIDF said that the exhibition would offer an opportunity to know well about the brilliant revolutionary career of President Kim Il Sung, wise leadership of Kim Jong Il and shining successes achieved by the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first secretary of the Maritime Territorial Regional Committee of the Communist Party of the Russian Federation and the chairperson of the Ugandan National Women's Council noted that the life of the President was a great life totally dedicated to the independence of Korea, its prosperity and happiness of the people. They stressed that Kim Jong Il is making a ceaseless journey for the Songun leadership as a faithful successor to the President's cause.

President of East Timor on Friendly Ties with DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- President of East Timor Kay Rala Xanana Gusmao extended thanks to the Korean people for their support to the struggle of the people of East Timor to build a new society when receiving credentials from the DPRK ambassador to East Timor on April 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that East Timor is attaching great importance to the development of the friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and East Timor and it would make all efforts to boost them.

Statement Released to Observe Anniversary of April 19 Popular Uprising  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front (AINDF) made public a statement on Thursday to observe the 47th anniversary of the April 19 Popular Uprising, according to Kuguk Jonson Internet site. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement noted that the April 19 Popular Uprising clearly proved that nothing can quell the desire and will of the people for independence, democracy and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle for independence against the U.S. has now reached a fresh turning phase thanks to the Songun politics of the north. But, the independent reunification desired by the valiant participants in the popular uprising has not yet come true. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has brought unbearable colonial disgrace and misfortune to the south Korean people for several generations, occupying south Korea for over six decades, and frantically pursued confrontation and war moves against the north, swimming against the trend of the June 15 era of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., in particular, is whipping together pro-American conservative forces forsaken by history in a desperate bid to help them wrest "power" through the forthcoming "presidential election" at any cost and thus tide over the crisis of its colonial rule and revive the rotten politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people can never be free from the yoke of colonialism nor can their desire for peace and reunification come true as long as the U.S. military presence and colonial rule over south Korea go on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people from all walks of life should intensify their struggle against the U.S. and war and for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces in the same spirit as displayed by the participants in the April 19 uprising. They should, at the same time, wage a bold struggle to decisively smash the moves of the pro-American conservative forces including the "Grand National Party" to return to power and thus bring back the dark era of fascism, dictatorship and division.

DPRK's Important Days Commemorated in Other Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- Political parties, governments, ministries, institutions, organizations and personages of different social standings in various countries sent floral baskets to the DPRK embassies in their countries to commemorate the Day of the Sun, the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and the 75th birthday of the heroic Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them were the Commission for External Affairs of the Central Committee of the Communist Party, the Foreign Ministry, the Defence Ministry, the Ministry of Public Security, the Ministry of Trade Commerce, the Central Committee of the Fatherland Front and the Union of Friendship Organizations of Vietnam, the Proletarian and Islamic Revolutionary Wounded Organization of Iran, the Iran Parties House and the Table-tennis Federation, the government of Geneva Canton of Switzerland, the Swiss Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, the "Doz" Company of the Czech Republic, the People's Democratic Party of Uzbekistan, the General Bureau of Intelligence of the Defense Ministry of Nigeria, the Workers' Party, the People's Socialist Party and the Socialist Popular Party of Mexico and the Mexican Fellowship Institute to Honor the Memory of President Kim Il Sung, the Emperor Group and the Golden Trip Travel Service Ltd of Hong Kong, China, the Senat Ship and Trading Private Limited Co. of Singapore, and the vice-president, the minister of Defence, the minister of Foreign Affairs, the minister of Information and the chief of the General Staff of the Armed Forces of Syria, the vice-chairman of the National Democratic Party, the minister of International Cooperation and the chairman of the National Progressive Unionist Party of Egypt, the chairman of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist) and the chief of Staff of Defence of the Nigerian Armed Forces.

Probe into Japan's Past Crimes Urged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The Council for the Solution of the Issue of the Volunteers' Corps and victims of the case of the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army in south Korea jointly released a statement on April 12 demanding that the Japanese government open to the public the truth behind the past crimes related to sexual servitude and make a legal compensation for them, according to a news report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement referred to the fact that the Tokyo Shimbun of Japan on April 11 disclosed the records on the trial of a Japanese war criminal, who was involved in the crime related to the "comfort women" case, asserting that the Japanese military directly ordered to install the "comfort stations".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement also said it has been clearly proved by a confidential document of the Dutch government, which was made public some time ago, that the imperial Japanese army violently took away women and detained them in "comfort stations" and, whenever "comfort women" ran away, brutally killed their families in retaliation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This goes to prove that the government and the military of Japan were fully involved in the case ranging from the coercive recruitment of "comfort women" to the operation of the "comfort stations," the statement said, adding: The facts show that Japanese Prime Minister Abe's remarks that "there is no hard evidence proving the coercive recruitment of "comfort women" were intended to downplay and cover up Japan's crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese government should stop its moves to downplay and conceal the crimes related to sexual servitude for the imperial Japanese army and fully open to the public the truth behind the crimes and make a legal compensation for them as soon as possible, it held.

Over 270 Political Parties Sign Pyongyang Declaration
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The Marxist-Leninist Reunification Communist Party of the Kyrgyzstan People, the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist) and the People's Liberation Front of Sri Lanka some time ago expressed full support for the Pyongyang Declaration "Let Us Defend and Advance the Cause of Socialism" on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of its adoption (in April 1992). And they confirmed their will to strengthen solidarity, international unity and cooperation with the progressive political parties of the world in the struggle to defend socialism on the basis of the principle of independence and equality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent five years, at least 20 political parties, including the Socialist Unionist Party of Syria, the Socialist Party of Mexico, the People's Rally for Socialism of Democratic Congo and the Misr Arab Socialist Party of Egypt, joined in signing the Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 So, the number of the parties which signed the declaration totals to over 270. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This evidently proves that the historic Pyongyang Declaration has displayed its great vitality in defending and advancing the cause of socialism.

Abrogation of "SOFA" Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The preparatory committee of the "Solidarity for Progress of South Korea" called a news conference in Seoul on April 12 and demanded the punishment of U.S. army criminals and the abrogation of the South Korea-U.S. "Status of Forces Agreement".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that two GIs belonging to the Second Division of the U.S. imperialist aggression forces in south Korea were nabbed while committing a sexual assault, the speakers at the news conference criticized the "government" for handing over the criminals to the U.S. forces side without punishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deploring that the "government" was looking on with folded arms at the crimes of U.S. soldiers which never ceased, they said it was because of the unequal "SOFA" between south Korea and the U.S.. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said the people should pool strength and get the "SOFA" scrapped and drive the U.S. forces out of this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the victims to U.S. soldiers' violence biggest in number were women, they said that all the women should turn out vigorously in the fight for the punishment of the U.S. army criminals and repeal of the "SOFA".

Iranian Military Attache Hosts Reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- Abdullah Jalali Nasab, military attache of the Iranian embassy here, hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Thursday to mark the Iranian Army Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were generals and officers of the Korean People's Army, officials concerned and diplomatic envoys and military attaches of embassies of different countries here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Charge d'Affaires A.I. Hossein Ali Entezari and staff members of the Iranian embassy were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Pyongyang Declaration, Banner of Victorious Socialist Cause
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- Fifteen years have passed since the historical Pyongyang Declaration was published. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On April 20, Juche 81 (1992), the representatives of political parties in different countries over the world adopted the Pyongyang Declaration titled "Let Us Defend and Advance the Cause of Socialism" in reflection of the desire of the progressive humankind to invariably take the road to socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upon its publication, progressive political parties around the world signed one by one, supporting it as a militant banner reflecting the desire of political parities and people for socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people and world progressive humankind have hardened their confidence in the victory of the socialist cause over the last years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist) and People's Liberation Front of Sri Lanka and others signed the Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il, with his energetic ideological and theoretical activities, has published famous works including "Abuses of Socialism Are Intolerable" and "Socialism Is a Science" to clarify the scientific accuracy and truth of socialism and indicate the tasks and way for the resurrection and victorious advance of the world socialist movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary people across the world are venerating him as the leader of the world socialist movement who has wisely led the Korean people with the great Songun politics to frustrate all sorts of challenges of the imperialists and reactionaries and to defend and develop the socialist cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Good Green Guyana, Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru and other various political parties have acclaimed him as honorary leader of their organizations for his energetic guidance over the global cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And many political parties including the All-Union Communist Party of Bolsheviks, Bangladesh People's League and New Communist Party of Britain adopted his famous works as must books of their parties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of the signatories to the declaration totals more than 270. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pyongyang Declaration, which confirms the truth and justice of the socialist cause and the inevitability of its final victory, instills the conviction of victory and revolutionary spirit into the minds of the world people advocating independence.

Brilliant Commander and His Invincible Armed Forces
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- Fifteen years have elapsed since Kim Jong Il was awarded the title of marshal of the DPRK.  The Korean army and people take this opportunity to look back with deep emotion upon the imperishable Songun revolutionary leadership exploits he has performed while protecting and adding brilliance to sovereignty and dignity of the country and nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has long taken President Kim Il Sung's idea and policy of attaching top priority to military affairs as his political one.  He started to carry forward the Songun revolution with his historic field guidance to the Guard Seoul Ryu Kyong Su 105 Tank Division of the Korean People's Army on August 25, Juche 49 (1960). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the first days of his leadership over the army, he implanted the loyalty to the leader in the minds of the KPA servicepersons as their life and soul and put forward the army building programme for transforming the entire army after the Juche idea in the 1970s so as to turn the KPA into one of the leader and Party in reality as well as in name. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA, the combat capacity of which has been strengthened in every way under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, has firmly defended socialism, smashing the U.S. imperialists' uninterrupted provocations including the spy ship Pueblo incident (1968), large-sized spy plane EC-121 incident (1969), Panmunjom incident (1976) and Panmunjom gunfight incident (1984) at each step. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With his deep penetration into the requirements of the changed international situation and revolution in the 1990s, he developed in depth the President's idea of attaching importance to arms, the military affairs and formulated the Songun politics as the basic mode of socialist politics and opened up a fresh phase for the development of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his Songun-based revolutionary leadership, the KPA has been strengthened into invincible revolutionary forces well equipped with modern offensive and defensive means, the destiny of the country and people firmly defended and the dawn of a great, prosperous and powerful nation broken. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA will in the future, too, demonstrate its might as the powerful revolutionary army of Mt.  Paektu as it is led by his great Songun revolutionary leadership.

Regional Consultation on Strengthening Health Systems Based on PHC Approach Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The WHO Southeast Asian Regional Consultation on Strengthening Health Systems based on PHC Approach was held at the People's Palace of Culture from April 18 to 20. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by a delegation of the Regional Office for South-East Asia of the World Health Organization led by Director Samlee Plianbangchang and delegations and delegates from the DPRK, Nepal, East Timor, Maldives, Myanmar, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Indonesia, India and Thailand, diplomatic envoys of various countries and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the consultation each participating country introduced its situation and experience gained as regards the issue of inter-sector cooperation, the issue of involving inhabitants, the issue of increasing the infrastructural capacity in the field of public health and the issue of cooperation with other fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There were also panel consultations on strengthening health systems. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A recommendation on PHC approach addressed to the WHO and the member nations in the Southeast Asian region was adopted at the consultation.

U.S. Accused of Contemplating Saber-Rattling against DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The United States has posed a serious military threat to the DPRK since it amassed offensive forces around it. It is self-evident that the latter can not approach the former's move with good faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson Friday observes this, commenting on the fact that the U.S. is contemplating joint naval maneuvers involving multinational forces, timed to coincide with the deployment of a huge carrier task force in the Pacific, and planning to conduct a drill of "intercepting missiles of north Korea" in collusion with Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. military moves in the Asia-Pacific region are targeted against the DPRK in the long run. The U.S. should refrain from any act of getting on the nerves of the DPRK, a dialogue partner, if the long pent-up distrust and hostility are to be wiped out and the groundwork of reconciliation and cooperation is to be laid. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has never discarded its sinister intention to stab delegates of the DPRK on their backs though the former sits at the negotiating table with the latter. The DPRK can not but conclude that it is the real intention of the U.S. not to miss the chance to stifle it by force of arms.

Anniversary of Pyongyang Declaration Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- The socialist cause is invincible for its truthfulness and validity and the Pyongyang Declaration is an inspiring banner stirring up the victorious advance of the socialist cause, states Rodong Sinmun Friday in an article dedicated to the 15th anniversary of the historic Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that 70 progressive political parties aspiring after socialism adopted and made public the Pyongyang Declaration "Let Us Defend and Advance the Cause of Socialism" on April 20, Juche 81 (1992), the author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of the political parties which signed the declaration has grown to over 270 today, 15 years after its publication. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various countries of the world have been the scene of incessant   struggle to rebuild socialism and push it forward energetically with the declaration as a banner of struggle. This attests to the attraction and invincibility of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The progressives worldwide gain firm conviction of the validity of the cause of socialism and the necessity of its triumph from the victorious advance of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are immensely encouraged by the victorious advance of Korean-style socialism today and fully determined to keep advancing the socialist cause with the declaration as a banner of struggle. Communist and workers' parties and progressive parties of different countries worldwide are waging a vigorous struggle to advance the socialist cause, while rallying all the independent forces at home and strengthening international solidarity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pyongyang Declaration is a common action programme of humankind which reflects the purpose, desire and interests of the people defending independence and powerfully arouses them to carry them into practice. The main guarantee for the victorious advance of the global cause of socialism lies in holding aloft the banner of the declaration and faithfully implementing it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unshakable will of the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean people to devote their all to the victory of the cause of socialism and the human cause of independence by implementing the Pyongyang Declaration.

Director of DPRK GDAE Sends Message to Director-General of IAEA
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 20 (KCNA) -- Ri Je Son, director of the General Department of Atomic Energy of the DPRK, on April 20 sent a message to Mohamed el-Baradei, director-general of the International Atomic Energy Agency, in connection with the fact that on April 17 the IAEA made a request for the DPRK visit of its working delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that when the director-general of the IAEA visited Pyongyang in March there was a preliminary understanding that the DPRK would invite the working delegation of the IAEA at an appropriate time, the message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK decided to suspend the operation of the nuclear facility in Nyongbyon within 60 days after the publication of the Feb. 13 agreement on the premise that the U.S. side should defreeze the DPRK's fund in Banco Delta Asia in Macao within 30 days after its publication. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK still remains unchanged in its will to implement the Feb. 13 agreement, but what matters is that it cannot move as the issue of frozen fund has not yet been completely settled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working negotiations are now brisk between a DPRK bank and the above-said bank to settle the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is ready to invite the above-said delegation of the IAEA the moment the actual defreezing of the frozen fund in the bank has been confirmed and discuss the issues of suspending the operation of the nuclear facility in Nyongbyon and verifying and monitoring procedures of it according to the Feb. 13 agreement.

Minju Joson condena la actitud de dos caras de EE.UU
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de abril (ATCC) -- La Republica Popular Democratica de Corea no puede ver con buenos ojos el comportamiento de Estados Unidos que la amenaza seriamente ubicando enormes fuerzas armadas de ataque en las periferias de la primera. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Minju Joson en un comentario individual del dia 20 y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al paralelo del emplazamiento concentrado en el Oceano Pacifico del colectivo de golpe al mando de un portaaviones, EE.UU. pretende desarrollar un simulacro conjunto maritimo junto con las fuerzas armadas multinacionales y probar en connivencia con Japon la "interceptacion de los misiles norcoreanos".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Todos estos movimientos militares, que se dan en la region de Asia y el Pacifico, apuntaran finalmente a la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para disipar la desconfianza y la hostilidad de largo tiempo y sentar la base de reconciliacion y cooperacion, es necesario que el imperio se abstenga de sus acciones que provocan a su contraparte (RPDC) del dialogo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque esta negociando con nuestro pais, EE.UU. no abandona nunca su maligna ambicion de dar una punalada en nuestra espalda. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La realidad obliga a nuestro pais a pensar que la verdadera intencion del imperio es atropellarnos por via militar en cualquier momento oportuno.

Rodong Sinmun se refiere a la Declaracion de Pyongyang
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de abril (ATCC) -- Con motivo del 15o aniversario de la publicacion de la historica Declaracion de Pyongyang, el periodico Rodong Sinmun publico este viernes un articulo individual que senala en particular: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los 70 partidos politicos progresistas aspirantes al socialismo aprobaron y publicaron el 20 de abril del 81 (1992) de la Era Juche la Declaracion de Pyongyang "Defendamos y llevemos adelante la causa socialista".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A lo largo de esos 15 anos de ahi para aca el numero de los partidos politicos firmantes sobrepaso 270. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En numerosos paises del mundo se despliega sin interrupcion la lucha por reconstruir el socialismo y llevarlo adelante tomandola por la bandera de la lucha, lo cual evidencia la vigencia y lo invencible de la sociedad de este tipo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Hoy dia, los pueblos progresistas del mundo ven en el avance victorioso del socialismo al estilo coreano la justeza y lo inevitable del triunfo de la causa socialista. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Muy estimulados por ello, tomaron la firme decision de llevar adelante la causa socialista considerando la Declaracion de Pyongyang como bandera de su lucha. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los partidos comunistas y del trabajo y los otros progresistas de diferentes latitudes del mundo agrupan a todas las fuerzas aspirantes a la independencia y fortalecen la solidaridad internacional para impulsar la causa socialista. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por tal razon, ese documento deviene el programa de lucha comun de la humanidad que refleja la aspiracion, el deseo y los intereses de los pueblos que abogan por la independencia y llama energicamente a estos a su materializacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La garantia fundamental del avance victorioso de la causa socialista mundial reside en marchar bajo la bandera de la Declaracion de Pyongyang y ejecutarla con fidelidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Partido del Trabajo y el pueblo de Corea tienen la inconmovible voluntad de ejecutarla consecuentemente para hacer todo lo que les corresponda en aras de la victoria de la causa socialista y la de independencia de la humanidad.

Namibia: obra de Kim Jong Il en folleto
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de abril (ATCC) -- La "Editorial de la Capital" en Windhoek de Namibia dio a luz el dia 13 en folleto la obra maestra del Dirigente Kim Jong Il, "El socialismo es ciencia", publicada el primero de noviembre del 83 (1994) de la Era Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta obra dilucida que el socialismo al estilo coreano, basado en la autoctona teoria socialista, resulta el mas cientifico y vital y aclara los problemas de principios que se presentan para defender el socialismo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En su prologo, el folleto destaca que la sociedad que desea la humanidad es precisamente el socialismo y que este ideal ya es una realidad en la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Anade que los visitantes a Corea veran con sus propios ojos un gran pais y un gran pueblo que llevan una vida optimista, feliz y amistosa disfrutando bajo el regimen socialista de muchos beneficios, inimaginables en otra sociedad, como la asistencia medica y ensenanza gratuitas.
